WEBVTT

00:00:04.191 --> 00:00:06.678
Hello, welcome to the TED Interview.

00:00:06.702 --> 00:00:07.913
I'm Chris Anderson.

00:00:07.937 --> 00:00:09.319
This is the podcast series

00:00:09.343 --> 00:00:11.709
where I get to sit down
with a TED speaker,

00:00:11.733 --> 00:00:14.593
we get to dive much deeper
into their ideas

00:00:14.617 --> 00:00:17.489
than was possible
during their short TED talk.

00:00:18.012 --> 00:00:22.437
Today, I am delighted
to have with us Daniel Kahneman.

00:00:23.094 --> 00:00:26.490
Danny Kahneman is truly
one of the greatest minds of our time.

00:00:26.971 --> 00:00:32.459
He won a Nobel Prize in 2002
for his work on behavioral economics,